Miscellany and regression
By Tom builder
The step taken by the college
last Week to join the city in
switching to “fast” or “daylight savings” time must be
viewed with mixed emotions.
It is heartwarming to have
proof that some college offer
girls are aware that there is a
world outside of, the college.
Nevertheless, it is readily apparent that this recent decision by the college was made in
a highly nasty manner without
proper consideration of the
implications interest in the
switching of time.
First of all, there is the surely practical consideration oi the
changing of the clocks. automatically, before the switch
Grinnell was (in Central stand
and time. About the! only thing
standard about time at Grillhell was that at any given instant no two Grinnell College
clocks showed the same time.
One library clock was on daylight saving time three weeks
ago.
When one told somebody the
time he had to be sure to spec»
ify which Clock he was using as
a basis. The United States has
{our time zones. Grinnell has
Well over 30.
But the problem of synchror
living the clocks pages to insignificance when compared to
 
other problems created by the
switch which may well have
proposed effects on the sociological lives of the cornell students. .
For example, those couples
who have been dating regularly
are upset because there will be
an hour less of darkness before women’s hours. They
would have preferred a south
to “daylight waiting" or ‘slow”
time.
But perhaps the most significant influence the change Will
have will be in the area of
study habits. And here the ei—
fact could be disastrous. For I
venture to say that the normal
student Will tend to use the ex—
try hour of straight for purposes of recreation rather than
study. As a result, the quality
of Work will decrease and the
reputation of the college Willsuffer. i
It is still not too late for the
college to reverse its decision.
Some clocks are probably still
operating on standard time.
Some students are. cameras
and railroad stations operate
on standard time. So should
Grinnell College. Leave us not
be received by the specials
something for nothing reason
ing that contents that by using
“last" time we can save day—
light. Humbug!
 
